Heat olive oil in a 12" skillet over medium high heat. Saute onion, garlic, jalapeno and red pepper for 3-4 minutes. Add chicken sausage slices to the skillet and saute for an additional 2 minutes. Stir in the cumin, salt and pepper, cook 1 minute. Add the cooked brown rice, black & pinto beans, toss with a spoon. Pour in the chicken broth, sprinkle in the cilantro. Cook for 5 minutes or until the rice and beans are heated through.